    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You just used the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-adventures-in-etheirys.actions.Item.zJ3Jakto3oqJTLZR]{Limit Break} action.</p><p><strong>Duration</strong> [[@actor.flags.pf2e.limit-rank]] rounds</p><hr /><p>Your shield is your very soul, and your soul burns brightly. While this Limit Break is active, your shield does not take damage when you take the Shield Block reaction (it still shares damage with you, however). Additionally, your shield's hardness increases by your level and you gain an additional reaction each turn which you can use to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.jM72TjJ965jocBV8]{Shield Block}, which you can also use to interpose your shield and block an attack intended for an ally within 15 feet of you.</p>",
